          "_customHTML": "<section class=\"mbr-section article content1\">\n    \n    <mbr-parameters>\n    <!-- Block parameters controls (Blue \"Gear\" panel) -->\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Góra\" name=\"paddingTop\" min=\"0\" max=\"8\" step=\"1\" value=\"4\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Dół\" name=\"paddingBottom\" min=\"0\" max=\"8\" step=\"1\" value=\"0\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Width Content\" name=\"widthContent\" min=\"1\" max=\"4\" step=\"1\" value=\"2\">\n        <input type=\"color\" title=\"Kolor ta\" name=\"bgColor\" value=\"#ffffff\">\n    <!-- End block parameters -->\n    </mbr-parameters> \n\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <div class=\"media-container-row\">\n            <div class=\"mbr-text col-12 mbr-fonts-style\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-7\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-text\" data-multiline mbr-article mbr-class=\"{'col-md-6': widthContent == 1, 'col-md-8': widthContent == 2, 'col-md-10': widthContent == 3, 'col-md-12': widthContent == 4}\"><p>We already have the twenty-first century, a time of extremely rapid technological progress, but we still love what is brilliant in its simplicity. Games without electricity are triumphant, both children and adults are eager to reach for them. We like good, proven solutions thanks to which we can spend family time and at the same time very creatively. A great example of such an option is UNO gameplay. Well, but what exactly is this game about?\n</p><p>\n</p><p>First, a bit of history. It turns out that UNO has already had several decades of tradition behind it, for the first time the world came across this proposal in 1971. And immediately the advantages of the game were appreciated, which began to gain popularity with wildfire. Currently, it is sold around the world by the widely known brand Mattel.\n</p><p>\n</p><p>To play UNO, we need a special colored deck of cards (we will not play with a normal deck). The rules could be compared to those of the Macao game. How many people can fight in this case? A minimum of two people, a maximum of eight can sit at a table. And what about cards, what is worth knowing about them? Some of them are marked with numbers, while others have to be classified as functionals.</p></div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</section>",
